textBeforeTable: Typical Properties   Mobilcut 320: Synthetic (mineral oil-free) grinding fluid, primarily recommended for grinding of steels and cast iron. Mobilcut 250: Semi synthetic cutting fluid primarily intended for the machining of aluminum and aluminum alloys.  It  may also be used on a wide variety of ferrous materials where a more versatile fluid is required. Mobilcut 230: High performance, semi synthetic cutting fluid, primarily recommended for machining steels, easier to machine stainless steels, and cast iron in milling, tuning, sawing, boring, drilling and reaming. Mobilcut 210:   Machining of ferrous/non ferrous metals in centralized or individual machines.  Lower oil content for extra wettability and corrosion protection.  Well suited for cast iron machining and grinding. Mobilcut 140: Machining of aluminum and high machinability steels in o moderate to heavy duty operations such as milling, turning, sawing, boring, drilling and reaming where the lubricity of a soluble oil is desired. Mobilcut 100:  General machining of easy to machine steels and copper alloys in light to moderate duty machining operations such as milling, turning, sawing, boring, drilling and reaming. Applications   Enhances the workplace environment Neutral Odor Easy separation and removal of tramp oil Compatible with high performance Mobil Vactra Oil No slideway lubricants Potential to consolidate products and reduce inventories Wide Range of applicability Improves filterability and surface finish Good separability from fines Reduces machine maintenance and rework of materials High degree of corrosion protection
